narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This class is fantastic. Yale's Hebrew department is great, and you'll learn so much in one year than you'd ever think you could.
Anyone can take Hebrew. It is not as difficult as it seems.

I loathe Hebrew, so take everything I say with a grain of salt:- The course is a lot of work, but probably not more than most other L2 language classes.- Dina is organized (something Ayala is not), but frigid. If possible, go with another instructor.- Ayala is a sweetheart. Take Ayala. Love Ayala.There might be worse things you could do with your time than take Hebrew at Yale. I can't think of any, though.
